  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The conscript gains Ride as a class skill.</p>\n<p>In addition, the conscript gains a mount. This functions as a druid&#8217;s animal companion, using the conscript&#8217;s level as his effective druid level. This grants the conscript the service of a loyal and trusty steed to carry him into battle. The creature must be one that he is capable of riding and is suitable as a mount. GMs should approve suitable mounts.</p>\n<p>The conscript does not take an armor check penalty on Ride checks while riding this mount. The conscript&#8217;s mount is always considered combat trained and gains Light Armor Proficiency as a bonus feat.</p>\n<p>If the conscript releases their mount or their mount dies, they may find a new mount after 1 week. If the conscript is in the environment where the new mount typically lives or is domesticated, the conscript may instead gain their new mount in 24 hours.</p>\n",
